    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-04T21:18:39+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-04T21:18:39+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-04T10:48:39Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-04T10:48:39Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system over Tasmania will continue to move southeastwards to be centred southeast of Tasmania by Sunday allowing a trough over WA to link to a weak front south of the Bight to move over western and southern parts of SA later Sunday into Monday. Another high pressure system is expected to follow early next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW002" description="Yorke Peninsula" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-04T21:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-05T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-04T10:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-04T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Winds easterly 15 to 25 km/h.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-05T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-04-06T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-04T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-05T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers. The chance of a thunderstorm in the south in the late afternoon and evening. Winds east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h turning northerly during the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to around 17 with daytime temperatures reaching the mid to high 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:20am to 3:10pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-06T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-07T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-05T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-06T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. Slight chance of a shower. Winds northerly 15 to 20 km/h tending northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the morning then tending northwest to southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h in the middle of the day. Overnight temperatures falling to around 18 with daytime temperatures reaching around 30.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-07T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-06T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower. Winds south to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h tending south to southeasterly during the afternoon then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 15 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers, most likely in the morning and afternoon. Light winds becoming north to northwesterly 15 to 20 km/h during the day then turning east to northeasterly during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to around 13 with daytime temperatures reaching the low to mid 20s.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
